body_html:
Seems like l2_cache_size does not exist in the CPU info returned on your platform.

Could you paste the output of the following (you may need to pip install py-cpuinfo):

import cpuinfo
print(cpuinfo.get_cpu_info())

That will help determine how we can make the test get L2 cache information.
(Which would ultimately end up as a patch to https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/557c539/tensorflow/tools/test/system_info_lib.py#L99)

body:
Seems like `l2_cache_size` does not exist in the CPU info returned on your platform.

Could you paste the output of the following (you may need to `pip install py-cpuinfo`):
```python
import cpuinfo
print(cpuinfo.get_cpu_info())
```

That will help determine how we can make the test get L2 cache information.
(Which would ultimately end up as a patch to https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/557c539/tensorflow/tools/test/system_info_lib.py#L99)
